article.headline: LSU 77, Alcorn St. 45
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- Tasmin Mitchell, Storm Warren and Alex Farrer led a balanced scoring attack as LSU defeated Alcorn State 77-45 in a first-round game of the LSU Invitational on Thursday night. Mitchell, who played just 18 minutes, finished with 12 points and six rebounds for the Tigers (2-0). Mitchell made 4 of 6 field-goal attempts, and all four of his free throws. Warren, playing in just his second game, had a double-double with 11 points and 11 rebounds. He also recorded four blocked shots and two assists. Farrer, who made a pair of 3-pointers, also finished with 11 points. Troy Jackson was the only player to score in double figures for the Braves (0-3), notching 16 points. All but two of Jackson?s points came in the first half. Jarvis Williams, who averaged 15 points in Alcorn?s first two games, was held to a single basket.
